Toronto’s bank towers have long dominated the city’s skyline. Each of the big five banks have at least one, including Royal Bank of Canada’s shiny gold building, and Toronto-Dominion Bank’s monolith black slabs. But new buildings offering more open and eco-friendly spaces that cater to the growing cohort of millennial workers are springing up. 
